The paper focuses on improving entity retrieval on structured data, which is a task related to information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) systems. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a clustering approach, which involves machine learning techniques such as x-means and spectral clustering, indicating a potential connection to artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of features and optimization, which are common in natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach using experimental results, which suggests a connection to machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
